  \x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\"I tell you what,\" said the traffic officer; \"I've got it figured out, I believe. It's not an egg at all. It's made of concrete or something, and it is a fake. There couldn't be an egg that big.\"

  \x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\"Well, it looks that big, Papa,\" said Howard.

  \x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\"Now, Howard,\" cautioned Mama.

  \x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\"Well, why does all the water run out of it?\" asked Ed junior.

  \x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\"Oh, lots of times concrete'll sweat in hot weather, if it's poorly made,\" said Papa. \"It's porous, see, and soaks up moisture on cool nights. Then when it gets hot like this afternoon, the moisture collects and runs out. Kinda like a water pitcher. Capillary action, they call it.\"

  \x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\x{a0}\"Gee, Papa, you know everything, don't you, Papa?\"' said Howard.

